{"title_page": "Sonepur State", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=July 2017}}\n{{Infobox former subdivision\n|conventional_long_name =Sonepur State<br>Sonpur State\n|common_name = Sonpur\n|nation      = [[British India]]\n|subdivision = [[Princely State]]\n|era         =\n|year_start  = 1556\n|date_start  =\n|event_start =\n|year_end    = 1948\n|date_end    =\n|event_end   = [[Independence of India|Accession to the Union of India]]\n|event1      =\n|date_event1 =\n|p1          =\n|s1          = India\n|flag_p1     = \n|flag_s1     = Flag of India.svg\n|image_flag  =\n|image_coat  = Sonepur State CoA.jpg\n|image_map   = SonpurKart.jpg\n|image_map_caption = Sonepur State in the [[Imperial Gazetteer of India]]\n|stat_area1  = 2347\n|stat_year1  = 1901\n|stat_pop1   = 169,877 \n|footnotes   =\n}}\n'''Sonepur''' also known as '''Sonpur State''',<ref>{{cite EB1911 |wstitle=Sonpur |volume=25 |page=416}}</ref> was one of the [[princely state]]s of [[India]] during the period of the [[British Raj]]. Its ruler was entitled to a nine [[salute state|gun salute]].<ref>[http://members.iinet.net.au/~royalty/ips/s/sonepur.html Sonepur Princely State (9 gun salute)]</ref> Formerly it was placed under the [[Central India Agency]], but in 1905 it was transferred to the [[Eastern States Agency]].<ref> Malleson, G. B.: ''An historical sketch of the native states of India,'' London 1875, Reprint Delhi 1984</ref> Its capital was [[Sonepur, Odisha|Sonepur]], the only significant town in the area. The former state's territory is in the present-day [[Subarnapur district]], [[Odisha]].\n\n==History==\nSonepur state was founded in 1556. The state became a [[British protectorate]] on 13 December 1826. The ruling family was awarded with the title ''[[Raja Bahadur]]'' for services rendered to the British during the [[History of Sambalpur#Sambalpur uprising|Sambalpur uprising]].<ref> Great Britain India Office. ''[[The Imperial Gazetteer of India]]''. Oxford: Clarendon Press, 1908.</ref>  \nThe last ruler of this princely state signed the accession to the [[Dominion of India|Indian Union]] on 1 January 1948.{{Citation needed|date=August 2019}}  \n\n==Rulers==\n\nThe ancient rulers of Sonepur State bore the title of 'Raja'. The last two had the title of 'Maharaja'.<ref>[http://www.worldstatesmen.org/India_princes_K-W.html Princely States of India]</ref>\n====Rajas====\n\n*1680 \u2013 1700                Purusottam Singh Deo               (d. 1700)\n*1700 \u2013 1725                Raj Singh Deo                      (d. 1725)\n*1725 \u2013 1750                Achal Singh Deo                    (d. 1750) \n*1750 \u2013 1770                Divya Singh Deo                    (d. 1770)\n*1770 \u2013 1771                Jarawar Singh Deo                  (d. 1771)  \n*1771 \u2013 1786                Sobha Singh Deo                    (d. 1786) \n*1786 \u2013 1841                Prithvi Singh Deo                  (d. 1841) \n*1802 \u2013 1822                Rani Laxmipriya Devi (f) -Regent\n*1841 \u2013  9 September 1891         Niladhar Singh Deo                 (b. 1837 \u2013 d. 1891) \n*1841 \u2013 1847                Bapu Dalpat Rai -Regent\n*1847 \u2013 1855                Rani Gundicha Devi (f) -Regent     (d. af.1862)\n*11 Sep 1891 \u2013  8 August 1902  Pratap Rudra Singh                 (b. 1853 \u2013 d. 1902) \n* 8 August 1902 \u2013  8 November 1908  Bir Mitrodaya Singh Deo            (b. 1874 \u2013 d. 1937)\n\n====Maharajas==== \n* 8 November 1908 \u2013 29 April 1937  Bir Mitrodaya Singh Deo            (s.a.) (from 1 January 1918, Sir Bir Mitrodaya Singh Deo)\n*29 Apr 1937 \u2013 15 August 1947  Sudhansu Shekhar Singh Deo         (b. 1899 \u2013 d. 1963)\n\n==See also==\n*[[Eastern States Agency]]\n*[[Political integration of India]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://indiastamp.blogspot.com/2010/02/indian-princely-state-sonepur-fiscal.html Sonepur State \u2013 Heritage of Indian Stamps]\n{{coord|20.83|N|83.92|E|region:IN_type:landmark_source:kolossus-svwiki|display=title}}\n{{Princely states of the Eastern States Agency}}\n{{Princely states of India}}\n[[Category:Subarnapur district]]\n[[Category:History of Odisha]]\n[[Category:Princely states of India]]\n[[Category:States and territories disestablished in 1948]]\n[[Category:Rajputs]]\n[[Category:1948 disestablishments in India]]\n[[Category:1556 establishments in India]]\n{{india-hist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=July 2017}}\n{{Infobox former subdivision\n|conventional_long_name =Sonepur State<br>Sonpur State\n|common_name = Sonpur\n|nation      = [[British India]]\n|subdivision = [[Princely State]]\n|era         =\n|year_start  = 1556\n|date_start  =\n|event_start =\n|year_end    = 1948\n|date_end    =\n|event_end   = [[Independence of India|Accession to the Union of India]]\n|event1      =\n|date_event1 =\n|p1          =\n|s1          = India\n|flag_p1     = \n|flag_s1     = Flag of India.svg\n|image_flag  =\n|image_coat  = Sonepur State CoA.jpg\n|image_map   = SonpurKart.jpg\n|image_map_caption = Sonepur State in the [[Imperial Gazetteer of India]]\n|stat_area1  = 2347\n|stat_year1  = 1901\n|stat_pop1   = 169,877 \n|footnotes   =\n}}\n'''Sonepur''' also known as '''Sonpur State''',<ref>{{cite EB1911 |wstitle=Sonpur |volume=25 |page=416}}</ref> was one of the [[princely state]]s of [[India]] during the period of the [[British Raj]]. Its ruler was entitled to a nine [[salute state|gun salute]].<ref>[http://members.iinet.net.au/~royalty/ips/s/sonepur.html Sonepur Princely State (9 gun salute)]</ref> Formerly it was placed under the [[Central India Agency]], but in 1905 it was transferred to the [[Eastern States Agency]].<ref> Malleson, G. B.: ''An historical sketch of the native states of India,'' London 1875, Reprint Delhi 1984</ref> Its capital was [[Sonepur, Odisha|Sonepur]], the only significant town in the area. The former state's territory is in the present-day [[Subarnapur district]], [[Odisha]].\n\n==History==\nSonepur state was founded in 1556. The state became a [[British protectorate]] on 13 Dec 1826. The ruling family was awarded with the title ''[[Raja Bahadur]]'' for services rendered to the British during the [[History of Sambalpur#Sambalpur uprising|Sambalpur uprising]].<ref> Great Britain India Office. ''[[The Imperial Gazetteer of India]]''. Oxford: Clarendon Press, 1908.</ref>  \nThe last ruler of this princely state signed the accession to the [[Indian Union]] on 1 January 1948.{{Citation needed|date=August 2019}}  \n\n==Rulers==\n\nThe ancient rulers of Sonepur State bore the title of 'Raja'. The last two had the title of 'Maharaja'.<ref>[http://www.worldstatesmen.org/India_princes_K-W.html Princely States of India]</ref>\n====Rajas====\n\n*1680 \u2013 1700                Purusottam Singh Deo               (d. 1700)\n*1700 \u2013 1725                Raj Singh Deo                      (d. 1725)\n*1725 \u2013 1750                Achal Singh Deo                    (d. 1750) \n*1750 \u2013 1770                Divya Singh Deo                    (d. 1770)\n*1770 \u2013 1771                Jarawar Singh Deo                  (d. 1771)  \n*1771 \u2013 1786                Sobha Singh Deo                    (d. 1786) \n*1786 \u2013 1841                Prithvi Singh Deo                  (d. 1841) \n*1802 \u2013 1822                Rani Laxmipriya Devi (f) -Regent\n*1841 \u2013  9 Sep 1891         Niladhar Singh Deo                 (b. 1837 \u2013 d. 1891) \n*1841 \u2013 1847                Bapu Dalpat Rai -Regent\n*1847 \u2013 1855                Rani Gundicha Devi (f) -Regent     (d. af.1862)\n*11 Sep 1891 \u2013  8 Aug 1902  Pratap Rudra Singh                 (b. 1853 \u2013 d. 1902) \n* 8 Aug 1902 \u2013  8 Nov 1908  Bir Mitrodaya Singh Deo            (b. 1874 \u2013 d. 1937)\n\n====Maharajas==== \n* 8 Nov 1908 \u2013 29 Apr 1937  Bir Mitrodaya Singh Deo            (s.a.) (from 1 Jan 1918, Sir Bir Mitrodaya Singh Deo)\n*29 Apr 1937 \u2013 15 Aug 1947  Sudhansu Shekhar Singh Deo         (b. 1899 \u2013 d. 1963)\n\n==See also==\n*[[Eastern States Agency]]\n*[[Political integration of India]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://indiastamp.blogspot.com/2010/02/indian-princely-state-sonepur-fiscal.html Sonepur State - Heritage of Indian Stamps]\n{{coord|20.83|N|83.92|E|region:IN_type:landmark_source:kolossus-svwiki|display=title}}\n{{Princely states of the Eastern States Agency}}\n{{Princely states of India}}\n[[Category:Subarnapur district]]\n[[Category:History of Odisha]]\n[[Category:Princely states of India]]\n[[Category:States and territories disestablished in 1948]]\n[[Category:Rajputs]]\n[[Category:1948 disestablishments in India]]\n[[Category:1556 establishments in India]]\n{{india-hist-stub}}\n", "name_user": "DrKay", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixeddashesusing ascript, date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript, date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript, date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sonepur_State"}
{"title_page": "Ika-6 na Utos", "text_new": "{{short description|Philippine television series}}\n{{Distinguish|Ika-5 Utos}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox television\n| name = Ika-6 na Utos\n| image = Ika-6 na Utos title card.jpg\n| caption = Title card\n| show_name_2 = ''A Woman Scorned''\n| genre = {{plain list|\n* [[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]\n* [[Revenge]]}}\n| creator = {{plain list|\n* [[Dode Cruz|Richard \"Dode\" Cruz]]\n* [[RJ Nuevas]]}}\n| writer = {{Plainlist|\n* Richard \"Dode\" Cruz\n* Geng Delgado\n* Luningning Ribay}}\n| director = [[Laurice Guillen]]\n| creative_director = [[Roy C. Iglesias]]\n| starring = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Sunshine Dizon]]\n* [[Gabby Concepcion]]\n* [[Ryza Cenon]]}}\n| theme_music_composer = Len Calvo\n| opentheme = \"Sa Lahat ng Iba\" by [[Aicelle Santos]]\n| country = [[Philippines]]\n| language = [[Tagalog language|Tagalog]]\n| num_episodes = 383\n| list_episodes = List of Ika-6 na Utos episodes\n| executive_producer = Arlene D. Pilapil\n| producer = Mark Andrew Valdez\n| location = {{Plain list|\n* [[Quezon City]], Philippines\n* [[Cebu City]], Philippines\n* [[Batangas]], Philippines}}\n| cinematography = Jay Abello\n| editor = {{Plainlist|\n* Neil Stephen Cervantes\n* Ryan Balatbat}}\n| camera = [[Multiple-camera setup]]\n| runtime = 26\u201332 minutes\n| company = GMA Entertainment TV\n| network = [[GMA Network]]\n| picture_format = [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])\n| first_aired = {{start date|2016|12|5}}\n| last_aired = {{end date|2018|3|17}}\n| website = http://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/tv/ika_6_na_utos\n}}\n\n'''''Ika-6 na Utos''''' (pronounced as Ika-anim na Utos / international title: ''A Woman Scorned'' / {{translation|Sixth Commandment}}) is a [[Philippine television drama]] [[revenge]] series broadcast by [[GMA Network]]. Directed by [[Laurice Guillen]], it stars [[Sunshine Dizon]], [[Gabby Concepcion]] and [[Ryza Cenon]]. It premiered on December 5, 2016 on the network's Afternoon Prime line up replacing ''[[Oh, My Mama!]]'' and worldwide on [[GMA Pinoy TV]]. On April 1, 2017, it joined the network's Sabado Star Power sa Hapon line up replacing ''[[Case Solved]]''. The series concluded on March 17, 2018 with a total of 383 episodes. It was replaced by ''[[Contessa (TV series)|Contessa]]'' in its timeslot.\n\nThe series is streaming online on [[YouTube]].<ref>{{cite web|URL=http://www.gmanetwork.com/fullepisodes/home/ika_6_na_utos |title=Ika-6 Na Utos - Home - Full Episodes |accessdate=October 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Premise==\nRome and Emma have problems and when issues arise, their marriage starts to be in jeopardy. Rome eventually meets Georgia, who will become his mistress.<ref>{{cite web|URL=http://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/tv/ika_6_na_utos/about/ |title=Ika-6 na Utos |accessdate=March 16, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Cast and characters==\n{{multiple image\n|direction = vertical\n|align = right\n|image1 = Gabby Concepcion at the KC Concepcion Live US Concert Tour, November 2010.jpg\n|caption1 = Gabby Concepcion portrays Rome Fuentabella.\n|width1 = 150\n|image2 = Ryza Cenon in 2017.jpg\n|caption2 = Ryza Cenon portrays Georgia Ferrer.\n|width2 = 150\n}}\n\n<!--Official cast billing from GMA Network-->\n;Lead cast\n* [[Sunshine Dizon]] as Emma Doqueza de Jesus-Fuentabella<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vXr4j5Pmq3c |title=Ika-6 na Utos: Pagbulgar sa sikreto ni Georgia|author=GMA Network |date=July 17, 2017 |publisher=GMA Network |accessdate=September 2, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Gabby Concepcion]] as Jerome \"Rome\" Fuentabella<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x-IBdoIoy6E |title=Ika-6 na Utos: Rome, the savior |date=December 6, 2016 |publisher=GMA Network |accessdate=September 2, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Ryza Cenon]] as Georgia \"Adyang\" Ferrer <ref name=\"maldita\">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cKNmghyInB4 |title=Ika-6 na Utos: Malditang Georgia |date=December 5, 2016 |publisher=GMA Network |accessdate=September 2, 2017}}</ref>\n\n;Supporting cast\n* [[Mike Tan]] as Angelo Trinidad<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zO-FK0BgvYI |title=Ika-6 na Utos: Pagpatay ni Georgia kay Angelo |date=August 30, 2017 |publisher=GMA Network |accessdate=September 2, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Rich Asuncion]] as Flora \"Flor\" Trinidad\n* [[Daria Ramirez]] as Lourdes Doqueza-de Jesus\n* Carmen Soriano as Margarita vda. de Fuentabella<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wmkHNhZm6BI |title=Ika-6 na Utos: Monster mother-in-law |date=December 7, 2016 |publisher=GMA Network |accessdate=September 2, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Marco Alcaraz]] as Chandler Vasquez\n* [[Mel Martinez (actor)|Mel Martinez]] as Zeny \n* [[Arianne Bautista]] as Anselma \"Selma\" Del Rosario<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1bA_vWUwZxc |title=Ika-6 na Utos: Tiwalag na si Selma |date=July 26, 2017 |publisher=GMA Network |accessdate=September 2, 2017}}</ref>\n\n;Recurring cast\n* Zach Briz as young Austin\n* Odette Khan as Consuelo \"Loleng\" Domingo vda. de Guidotti\n* [[Marife Necesito]] as Vicky\n* Ollie Espino as Mando\n* Rosemarie Sarita as Mildred Ferrer<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7D60f8R0wbg |title=Ika-6 na Utos: Ang Kuwento ni Georgia |date=January 13, 2017 |publisher=GMA Network |accessdate=September 2, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Eunice Lagusad]] as Becca\n* Angelica Ulip as Milan de Jesus Fuentabella / Sydney Ferrer Fuentebella\n* [[Cai Cortez]] as Charlotte Amalie \"Char\" Ledesma\n* [[Pen Medina]] as Antonio \u201cNoel\u201d de Jesus\n* [[Angelika Dela Cruz]] as Geneva \"Gengen\" Ferrer-Takahashi<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iljf0XxwxTQ |title=Ika-6 na Utos: Geneva is coming |date=June 20, 2017 |publisher=GMA Network |accessdate=September 2, 2017}}</ref> \n* Jacob Briz as Austin de Jesus Fuentabella\n\n;Guest cast\n* [[Karel Marquez]] as Lara Salcedo-Fuentabella<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SYhuDEsOHFY |title=Ika-6 na Utos: Rome\u2019s tragic past |date=December 5, 2016 |publisher=GMA Network|accessdate=September 2, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Lito Legaspi]] as Allan\n* Toby Alejar as Orlando\n* Anna Marin as Anita<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=G6_qVXHBv8A |title=Ika-6 na Utos: Nakaw na halik |date=December 15, 2016 |publisher=GMA Network |accessdate=September 3, 2017}}</ref>\n* Marcus Madrigal as Dave\n* Sheila Marie Rodriguez as Cynthia\n* [[Allan Paule]] as Danilo\n* [[Luane Dy]] as a television host \n* Aprilyn Gustillo as Grace\n* [[Zoren Legaspi]] as Lyon Muller\n* [[Chynna Ortaleza]] as Maui Alcaraz\n* [[Leanne Bautista]] as Chelsea Muller\n* Lharby Policarpio as Morgan\n* [[Vince Gamad]] as Darwin\n* [[Elle Ramirez]] as Kenya\n* Marnie Lapuz as Chona\n* [[Bryan Benedict]] as Nato\n* Ranty Portento as Brian Santiago<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CfZBHk6HgVE |title=Ika-6 na Utos: Pagtuklas ni Emma sa katotohanan |date=July 12, 2017 |publisher=GMA Network |accessdate=September 2, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[SexBomb Girls#Former members|Izzy Trazona-Aragon]] as Alberta Alcaraz-Muller\n\n==Ratings==\nAccording to [[AGB Nielsen Philippines]]' Nationwide Urban Television Audience Measurement, the pilot episode of ''Ika-6 na Utos'' earned an\n11.9% rating.<ref>{{cite web|title=AGB: 10 Top-rating Pilot and Finale Daytime episodes in 2016 |author=Ching, Mark Angelo |date=January 1, 2017 |url=https://www.pep.ph/guide/tv/25268/agb-10-top-rating-pilot-and-finale-daytime-shows-in-2016 |accessdate=January 24, 2018}}</ref> While the final episode scored an 8.6% rating.<ref>{{cite web|title=AGB RATINGS: GMA-7 nearly sweeps daytime block |url=https://www.pep.ph/guide/tv/27817/agb-ratings-gma-7-nearly-sweeps-daytime-block |date=April 25, 2018 |accessdate=June 4, 2018}}</ref> The series had its highest rating on people in television homes on July 28, 2017 with a 10.7% rating.<ref>{{Cite web|title=July 28 (Fri) TV Ratings / AGB Nielsen / NUTAM (Afternoon). |url=http://www.pep.ph/news/pepalerts/read/20782 |accessdate=July 28, 2017}}</ref> Based from Television Audience Measurement audience shares among people in television home, the series had its highest rating on February 16, 2018 with a 57.5% rating.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Ika-6 na utos got groundbreaking rating in afternoon show according to AGB Nielsen Phils.(TAM) |url=https://m.facebook.com/story.php?story_fbid=1822942097756935&id=509798835737941 |accessdate=March 19, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Accolades received by ''Ika-6 na Utos''\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Recipient\n! Result\n! Ref.\n|-\n| rowspan=13 | 2017\n| rowspan= 3 | 7th OFW Gawad Parangal\n| Best Actress\n| [[Sunshine Dizon]]\n| {{Won}}\n| rowspan= 3 | \n<ref>http://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/showbiznews/news/35422/sunshine-dizon-gabby-concepcion-at-wowowin-ilan-sa-pinarangalan-sa-7th-ofw-gawad-parangal/story</ref>\n|-\n| Best Actor\n| [[Gabby Concepcion]]\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| Best Supporting Actress\n| [[Ryza Cenon]]\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| Gawad Amerika Awards\n| Most Outstanding Filipino Actress in TV\n| Sunshine Dizon\n| {{Won}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|title=WATCH: Sunshine Dizon, tatanggap ng Best Actress Award sa Amerika para sa 'Ika-6 Na Utos' |url=https://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/tv/ika_6_na_utos/35270/watch-sunshine-dizon-tatanggap-ng-best-actress-award-sa-amerika-para-sa-ika-6-na-utos/story |website=gmanetwork.com |accessdate=November 16, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan= 4 | [[31st PMPC Star Awards for Television]]\n| Best Daytime Drama Series\n| ''Ika-6 na Utos''\n| {{Nom}}\n| rowspan= 4 |<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.pep.ph/guide/tv/26962/31st-star-awards-for-tv-nominees-revealed-joshlia-jakbie-to-receive-special-awards|title=31st Star Awards for TV nominees revealed; JoshLia, JakBie to receive special awards|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]|last=Anarcon|first=James Patrick|date=October 30, 2017|accessdate=November 12, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Drama Actor\n| Gabby Concepcion\